
Method:   Function


public static void main(String[] args) {
    declaring a method:
    Access modifiers        Specifier   Return Type     Method name(Parameter)

    }

    Access modifier   public, private, protected, default
    Specifier:  static, final, abstract, sychronized
    Return Type: void, Any Data Type
    Method : can be any name
    parameter: any data type

    //Student st1=new Student();



Method Overloading

    -Multiple different methods sharing the same method name
    -Same method name, different parameters
    -Return type, access modifiers, specifiers can ve same or different

    Advantages

    1. easy to memorize
    2. easy to read
    3. reusable
    4. flexible



